I have mixed feelings on this starter relic. The free stance entry is nice, and it makes your execute be online in every fight. On the other hand, your act 1 is generally really good already due to vigor stacking, and you have several very good front loaded damage cards available to you on Champ that can easily be picked up in act 1. You also already have access to berserker and defensive shout, and you're fairly likely to draw one of those before execute in most act 1 fights, so it's usually still online, and unlike zap for defect, they cost 0 by default, so casting them is much easier. Once you start adding more finishers (and cards in general) to your deck, champions crown free stance entry becomes more useful, as it's harder to draw the shouts for an early stance entry, and you have more cards that can be dead if you are stanceless.

The thing is, victorious crown is an awful boss relic to see at least 90 percent of the time, and champ desperately wants the 4th energy ASAP (and can benefit from having 5 energy), so there are significant benefits to swapping this out at the heart bonus. Even if you miss the 4th energy, or get a particularly bad swap, champs act 1 is strong enough that you can probably power through and get another chance after beating the act 1 boss. I think champions crown effect is pretty replaceable (just drafting a few reasonable stance entry cards mimics the effect reasonably well), and that champs difficult late game really can benefit from having the extra boss relic, so I generally favor swapping. The effect just isn't strong enough, and you don't really need it's help to crush acts 1 and 2.

Is the chance of being offered a relic swap in your boss rewards really high enough to influence your decision? It's going to happen in a small percentage of runs and even when it does you have two other choices.

I would say that it's only a small factor, but I do believe that victorious crown is that bad. The more important element is that you get an extra shot at finding one of the really impactful boss relics, both during the actual swap, and when you reach the act 1 and 2 boss chests
Is victorous crown as bad as ring of the snake evo?
victorious crown has a negative attached and recreates the problem champions crown tries to solve
ring of snake is just uninspiring
and both are just not energy
victorious crown is DEFINITELY not energy

Ring of the serpent is very good, it's just rare that you get to take it, since drawing 6 cards a turn isn't very useful if you don't already have the 4th energy, a lot of 0 cost cards, or some kind of really good synergies involving tactician and concentrate. Also ring of the snake gives you a better turn 1, so you are technically nerfing yourself during that first turn, and only breaking even on the second turn.

I'm not a big fan of this. While this does let you use execute if you are unlucky enough to draw it without one of your 2 shouts first this relic starts to falls off past the first 20 floors you climb. When you start taking more stance entry cards you also run into the problem of this relic barely  doing anything when you start with one in your hand. Half of the stance changing cards ether 0 or are inanimate anyways so this happens a lot. The crown smooths over early game RNG but its value will plummet when you have a couple of stance dances. Swapping this is very appealing, you ditch your relic that does not have long term value with one that will. Its even better if you hit an energy relic (which is like a 60% chance) since champ really values having 4 energy since he has so many 2 cost cards that you want (much like ironclad does) starting the game with 4 energy can completely change the way you take on act 1.
So I am regularly boss swapping as champ, I will take remove/transform 2 instead if that is offered though.

I don't see myself boss swapping as champ ever, playing execute is so important to your early game and even if you draw a stance entering card in the same hand as your finisher you can just get the finisher bonus and then re enter a stance,

I'm saying all of this after praising execute like yesterday. I still think its good without having this starter relic. I think champions crown is roughly equivalent to one card draw in value on turn one, since its effectively playing a stance dance for you before the fight starts. Thats not insignificant but it is worse then a boss relic to the point were i'm willing to roll the dice
it still provides 3 skill bonuses and a finisher bonus even if you ignore execute not being a dead draw

3 skill bonuses just aren't that much in the grand scheme of a fight, its like a 50% chance of being almost an aekobeko (however you spell that thing). Sometimes I don't even get all 3 bonuses since I end up switching to the other stance early because I need its finisher bonus instead.

I think champions crown be better designed if it gave you a retainable stance dance at the start of each fight, that way you get to at least choose which stance you start in and can keep it for another turn if necessary
